// // This module implements a binary classifier using an SVM-style decision boundary. It takes three 1-bit inputs and produces a 1-bit output. If the sum of the inputs is less than or equal to 1, it outputs 1 (positive class); otherwise, it outputs 0 (negative class).
module svm_classifier (  
    input wire feature1,  
    input wire feature2,  
    input wire feature3,  
    output wire classification  
);  
    assign classification = (feature1 + feature2 + feature3) > 1 ? 1'b1 : 1'b0;  
endmodule
